An AR15, or any kind of rifle, would not be my choice for home
protection.  But if that is the only gun you have.....

If you live in an apartment building or in a house with neighbors on
all sides, you should be concerned about excessive penetration through
3 or 4 walls after it goes through the burglar.  Can you find some
hollow point ammo?

Most home protection emergencies occur at night, and you do not want
any flashlights or red dots to give the intruder a fix on your
position.  The range inside the house will be very short, and if you
can see him you can hit him without sights.  And remember: this is not
the time to start a conversation.  Just knock him down and you can
talk all you want with the police.

