Well, allow me to go out on a limb here by risking the ire of all the
AR-15 fan club brigades, but I think you would be better served with a
pump 12 gauge shotgun using number 9 shot instead.
Why bird shot?
Penetration issues.
That is that any stray pellets will generally not penetrate standard
drywall structures, thus preventing collateral damage to bystanders or
family members.
Also, believe me, bird shot at home defense ranges is just as deadly as
00 buck or (worse) your AR-15 with hollowpoint or softpoints, without
risking overpenetration.
Bad guys will drop to the equivalent of an entire revolver of .38
specials striking all at once.
I'm not questioning the power of the .223, but I think you would be
better served by something with still more knockdown power and limited
penetration.
