Matt, nothing you mention above is essential however we do have a
tendency to get dazzled by foot work when it comes to accessories so
we convince ourselves more or less to keep up with the Jone's. You've
been shooting your rifle several times a month so by now you would be
best to say what improvements you want. One of my first improvements
was to install one of those wedge spacer things (forgot the name) that
lake up the room between the web of my hand and the rear top of the
hand-grip. Without it I was getting too much finger across the
trigger.

My second choice was to change the pistol grip to a Hogue
http://www.dallastacticalsupplies.com/RSR_Images/HO15000_1.JPG
but in retrospect a Urgo grip may of been better because it also takes
up the space between the grip and hand and killing both birds.
http://aceltdusa.com/images04/AR15/ERGOGrip_M16E_med.jpg

As for your question on a dot sight, how's your peepers? In my younger
days peep sights were fine but father time is taking its toll so I
opted for a Leupold/Gilmore dot sight w/4moa dot. It may not be one of
the best (expensive) ones going but leaps and bounds over the $35
dollar specials http://www.nealjguns.com/ss_store/media/39LG35TT2.jpg

I'd suggest if you going to install any type of optics I would also
recommend putting it on a quality mount. My Bushmaster is of the A2
configuration so my carry handle mount is a A.R.M.S.#2 It also has a
generous opening beneath the sight should the batteries go dead and
the iron sight is needed http://www.armsmounts.com/catalog.php?action=124&amp;item;_id=1

Lastly and for our type of general use not really needed (one of those
Jone's things) I bought a Jewell trigger
http://www.knsprecisioninc.com/Images/Jewell%20Trigger%20Systems.jpg
I've found with usege stock AR triggers settle in fairly well for
typical general shooting but if you want to get technical an ajustable
trigger is a nice improvement.

With that particular rifle that's as far as I chosen to go for it's
intended need but obviously just the tip of the accessory iceberg,
it's a matter of what you need vs what you want. If you are intending
to buy on-line do plenty of price checking because some items may
differ from $20+ or-dollars depending on what sight your looking at,
also the pic addresses above weren't meant for endorsement, just to
give you a visual. have fun...

