To make your rifle a bit handier for this situation a shorter barrel and an
optical sight would be a good idea. Even better buy a M-4 clone and put an
optical sight on it. Even better:
http://www.bushmaster.com/catalog_xm15_BCWVMF16M4ORC.asp While I am not an
expert a handgun would probably better suit your needs.

Some thoughts on you post:

A rifle is better suited for distance. If your problem is far enough away
you need a rifle it might be hard to claim you felt your life was
threatened.

A rifle might be slower to bring on target.

The ugly black rifle might make a prosecutor consider some part of your
defense excessive. You have to survive the shooting and what follows; going
to jail decreases your odds of survival.

Other posters have mentioned overpenetration and that is a real concern with
a rifle. http://www.theboxotruth.com/docs/bot1.htm Putting a medium sized
pig between the rifle and the box would probably be educational; you would
know what to expect if you hit the target.

Coming around a corner with a rifle will give an intruder advance warning of
your presence.

The space between the front sight and the flash hider is long enough to get
a good grip and force the muzzle off target.

The flash hider would probably help your intruder maintain a grip on the
barrel if you were trying to pull the rifle away from them. Pulling back on
the rifle while they were holding on to it would probably put the muzzle
over some part of their anatomy guaranteeing a hit.
George in Las Vegas

