John there is no such thing as 100% on any of the topics we are discussing.
I've seen frangibles fail to come apart as they're supposed to.  So none of it
is going to work _ALL_ the time, period.  It's a simple fact of life.  In this
case, close enough is all you're ever going to get.  Even your shotgun/handgun
perusasion falls into that category and if you think otherwise, you're fooling
yourself.

I am going with the odds and the odds are that .223 rounds are not going to
overpenetrate at the ranges we're talking about.  The odds are also very high
that it's going to stop a human in their tracks.  I have absoultely no concern
of overpenetration, other than a hole in the wall to patch if it does or if I
miss.  The same applies to a handgun or shotgun, except with the shotgun there
might be extra holes.
